The paper deals with quantitative games, which are a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also introduces a new technique for solving such games, which involves structuring the space of games and reducing them to vertex-ranked games. This technique involves the use of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and has applications in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for computing fault-resilient strategies. Finally, the paper also discusses the theoretical foundations of the technique, which involves logic and set theory (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL).
